ENTRY            F0596   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0596001   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  8         29
TITLE      Investigation of large angle elastic and inelastic
           alpha particles scattering on Si isotopes
AUTHOR     (A.Grzeszczuk,J.Czakanski,J.Kisiel,B.Kozlowska,
           M.Siemaszko,A.Surowiec,W.Zipper,A.Budzanowski)
INSTITUTE  (3POLIFJ,3POLSLS)
REFERENCE  (J,APP/B,25,849,1994)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3POLIFJ) U-120
DETECTOR   (PS) The position sensitive detector (PSD) was placed
           in the region of backward angles as close as possible
           to the beam. The angular range covered by the sensitive
           surface of the PSD was between 161 and 173 degr. in the
           lab. system.
           Parameters of PSD:
           Sensitive surface            51*8 mm
           Thickness of sensitive layer  0.5 mm
           Energy resolution             0.1 MeV
           Position resolution           0.38 mm
           Working voltage               +170 V
           Working temperature           -30 +25 degr.
           Vacuum                        10E-4-10E-5 T
           (SOLST) Solid state detector of 500 um thickness was
           placed at 158 degr.(lab). It served as a monitor
           detector for beam measurements and for cross sections
           normalization.
SAMPLE     All silicon targets used in the experiment were
           prepared by the Target Laboratory of the Munich
           University.
HISTORY    (20031021C)
           (20251216U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              29
COMMON               1          3
EN-RSL
KEV
  200.0
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           36
